Issues intentionally left unpatched
----------------------------------------------------------------
- WireHookExecutor does not call `sender.cancel` when its own
  abort/timeout race wins. The underlying ReverseRpcClient's
  cancelPendingRequest drains the router map from the sender
  side via its own timeout, so the leak is bounded at
  `hookTimeoutMs` — not a correctness bug, just not ideal.
- `kimi --session <id> --wire` does not surface an error; the
  wire server ignores `opts.session` because id routing happens
  over the wire protocol itself. CLI flag documentation gap,
  not a regression.
- Two pre-existing "not yet implemented" strings in
  apps/kimi-cli/src/wire/kimi-core-client.ts (runtime model /
  agent live-switch) are Phase 19 §C scope, flagged in the
  per-slice commits.
